# Teddy Warner

> Thiel Fellow and founder of Intempus, building emotionally intelligent robots. Engineer specializing in rapid prototyping and applied AI, based in San Francisco.

Teddy Warner is the CEO and Founder of Intempus, a company developing expressive, emotionally intelligent robots. He is a 2025 Thiel Fellow and a graduate of the Fab Academy.

Previously, Teddy worked at Midjourney conducting research for their internal hardware effort. His expertise spans mechatronics engineering, PCB development, CAD design, physical computing, and rapid prototyping.

His technical work includes the Von Niemann Probe (a chess cheating investigation device), Assistive Aquaponics (automated ecosystem monitoring), UPDI Serial Programers, and other fun, more whimsical projects. He writes essays exploring technology, robotics adoption, and philosophy.
